[2] Cholera - Uganda (Kisoro)
Date: Tue, 2 Jan 2007
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: New Vision [edited]
<http://www.newvision.co.ug/D/8/18/540827>

Cholera has hit Kisoro district, killing 3 people, reports Darious
Magara. About 40 others were by Mon, 1 Jan 2007 admitted in hospitals in
critical conditions, hospital officials revealed. The district director of
health services, Dr. Assay Ndizihirwe, said 2 women and one child died in
Kisoro Hospital over the weekend.
He said the cholera outbreak was intensified by unhygienic living
conditions of Congolese refugees at Bunagana, on the border with the
Democratic Republic of Congo. Ndizihirwe confirmed that most of the
victims were Congolese nationals who crossed to Uganda late in 2006 fleeing
fighting there.
Sources at the border said some of the victims had been transferred to
camps but other hundreds were still living at the Bunagana border.
Ndizihirwe appealed to NGO, international relief agencies and the
Government to come to their rescue. He said the district lacks the
capacity to handle hundreds of refugees at the border.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[Kisoro is a small district in extreme southwestern Uganda bordering on
Congo DR and Rwanda. It can be found on a map of Uganda at:
<http://www.un.org/Depts/Cartographic/map/profile/uganda.pdf>. - Mod.LL]
